node.text:
I got a lot of questions/comments about the power steering fluid I used because the old cap said “ATF Only”. Since I read the comments of all my videos, I think this is a good one to make a video on! 
The reservoir cap on some BMWs does read “ATF ONLY”. But since 1991 Pentosin started recommending the use of CHF 11S Synthetic Power Steering fluid instead of the CHF 7.1 Power Steering Fluid which used a mineral oil base and is now discontinued.  Pentosin is the OEM supplier of power steering fluid for BMW.
 
While ATF works, the down side is it could eventually cause the seals and hoses to harden and create cracks and leaks in the power steering system.  That’s why I used synthetic power steering fluid instead of ATF.

Code “90AToff” gives you guys $90 off. Link in bio if you want your own scoot scoot! It goes about 15-17mph cruise and the battery lasts about 10miles if you’re flooring it all the time, which you should be or you’re not driving a scooter properly. With a name like TurboAnt you can’t go wrong! These 🐌🐜’s are attention grabbers for sure. I get sooo many looks riding this bad boy. I ride around town with my helmet and people point and take pics. Scoot scoots are also great conversational pieces. And don’t get me started with the ladies... they always ask “can I try?” so you’re going to have to be ready to say NO! I see why @richiebkidd love electric stuff. It’s fun! 
#ChrisFix #electric #scooter #ScootScoot #TurboAnt #🐌🐜

Instead of pumping out videos, I’ve focused on making videos that cover everything in one video with the best camera angles, everything in focus, and with the most clear and concise audio I can produce. No fluff, no tangents, just focused, accurate information for you guys to learn from. That way when you click on a ChrisFix video about how to change brakes, you know you’re going to learn everything you need to know on how to change brakes so you can do it yourself.
